1.4 Data Cleaning

1.4.1 Clean and standardize field names
compustat_global_clean <- compustat_global_df %>%
  clean_names() %>%
  mutate(
    isin = str_trim(isin),
    fyear = as.numeric(fyear)
  )

compustat_na_clean <- compustat_na_df %>%
  clean_names() %>%
  mutate(
    tic = str_trim(tic),
    fyear = as.numeric(fyear)
  )

refinitiv_clean <- refinitiv_df %>%
  clean_names()

worldbank_clean <- worldbank_df %>%
  clean_names()

compustat_global_prices_clean <- compustat_global_prices_df %>%
  clean_names()
1.4.2 Filter USA and EU countries

I am keeping only the EU Member States and USA data.

sample_country_codes <- c(
  "AUT", "BEL", "BGR", "HRV", "CYP", "CZE", "DNK", "EST", "FIN", "FRA",
  "DEU", "GRC", "HUN", "IRL", "ITA", "LVA", "LTU", "LUX", "MLT", "NLD",
  "POL", "PRT", "ROU", "SVK", "SVN", "ESP", "SWE", "USA"
)

compustat_na_clean <- compustat_na_clean %>%
  filter(fic %in% sample_country_codes)
compustat_global_clean <- compustat_global_clean %>%
  filter(fic %in% sample_country_codes)
compustat_global_prices_clean <- compustat_global_prices_clean %>%
  filter(fic %in% sample_country_codes)
1.4.3 Merge stock prices
# Add price_year
compustat_global_clean <- compustat_global_clean %>%
  mutate(price_year = if_else(fyr == 12, fyear, fyear - 1))

# Prepare prices df
compustat_global_prices_clean <- compustat_global_prices_clean %>%
  mutate(
    datadate = dmy(datadate),
    year = year(datadate),
    month = month(datadate)
  ) %>%
  group_by(gvkey, year, month) %>%
  slice_max(order_by = datadate, n = 1, with_ties = FALSE) %>%
  ungroup()

# Join prices
compustat_global_clean <- compustat_global_clean %>%
  left_join(
    compustat_global_prices_clean %>% select(gvkey, year, month, prccm),
    by = c(
      "gvkey" = "gvkey",
      "price_year" = "year",
      "fyr" = "month"
    )
  ) %>%
  rename(prcc_f = prccm)
1.4.4 Reshape Refinitiv data to panel format
year_cols <- grep("^y20\\d{2}$", colnames(refinitiv_clean), value = TRUE)

refinitiv_long <- refinitiv_clean %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = all_of(year_cols),
    names_to = "year",
    values_to = "esg_value"
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    year = as.numeric(str_extract(year, "\\d{4}")), # extract the numeric year
    variable = str_trim(datatype),
    isin = str_trim(isin_code),
    tic = str_trim(ticker_symbol)
  ) %>%
  select(name, country, isin, tic, sic_code, year, variable, esg_value)

refinitiv_wide <- refinitiv_long %>%
  pivot_wider(
    id_cols = c(isin, tic, year),
    names_from = variable,
    values_from = esg_value
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    isin = str_trim(isin),
    tic = str_trim(tic),
    year = as.numeric(year)
  )

# Split into North America (NA) and Global based on ISIN prefix
refinitiv_wide_na <- refinitiv_wide %>%
  filter(grepl("^US", isin))

refinitiv_wide_global <- refinitiv_wide %>%
  filter(!grepl("^US", isin))
1.4.5 Merge ESG data to Compustat
compustat_isin <- left_join(
  compustat_global_clean,
  refinitiv_wide_global,
  by = c("isin", "fyear" = "year")
)

compustat_tic <- left_join(
  compustat_na_clean,
  refinitiv_wide_na,
  by = c("tic", "fyear" = "year")
)
1.4.6 Combine NA & Global datasets
all_columns <- union(names(compustat_isin), names(compustat_tic))

# Identify missing columns in each
missing_in_df <- setdiff(all_columns, names(compustat_isin))
missing_in_na <- setdiff(all_columns, names(compustat_tic))

# Add missing columns
compustat_isin_fixed <- compustat_isin %>%
  mutate(!!!setNames(rep(list(NA), length(missing_in_df)), missing_in_df))

compustat_tic_fixed <- compustat_tic %>%
  mutate(!!!setNames(rep(list(NA), length(missing_in_na)), missing_in_na))

# Reorder columns to match
compustat_isin_fixed <- compustat_isin_fixed %>% select(all_of(all_columns))
compustat_tic_fixed <- compustat_tic_fixed %>% select(all_of(all_columns))

compustat_combined <- bind_rows(compustat_isin_fixed, compustat_tic_fixed) %>%
  select(-consol, -popsrc, -datafmt, -costat, -pstk) # get rid of not important fields

compustat_combined <- compustat_combined %>%
  mutate(ni = coalesce(ni, nicon)) %>% # merge into ni
  mutate(csho = coalesce(csho, cshoi)) %>% # merge into ni
  select(-nicon, -cshoi) # drop nicon after merging
1.4.7 Merge macroeconomic indicators
# Clean names and ensure consistent types before reshaping
worldbank_clean <- worldbank_df %>%
  clean_names()

# Identify the year columns (e.g., x2008 to x2024)
year_cols <- grep("^x20\\d{2}", names(worldbank_clean), value = TRUE)

# Coerce all year columns to numeric to avoid pivot_longer() type conflict
worldbank_clean[year_cols] <- lapply(worldbank_clean[year_cols], as.numeric)

# Now proceed as originally planned
macro_long <- worldbank_clean %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = all_of(year_cols),
    names_to = "year",
    values_to = "value"
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    year = as.numeric(str_extract(year, "\\d{4}")),
    series_name = str_to_lower(series_name) %>% str_trim()
  ) %>%
  select(country_name, country_code, series_name, year, value)

# Simplify series names to readable column headers
macro_long <- macro_long %>%
  mutate(
    series_clean = case_when(
      str_detect(series_name, "gdp \\(current") ~ "gdp_current_usd",
      str_detect(series_name, "gdp growth") ~ "gdp_growth",
      str_detect(series_name, "unemployment") ~ "unemployment_rate",
      str_detect(series_name, "deflator") ~ "inflation",
      str_detect(series_name, "real interest") ~ "interest_rate",
      str_detect(series_name, "rule of law") ~ "rule_of_law",
      TRUE ~ "other"
    )
  ) %>%
  filter(series_clean != "other") # Keep only the 6 I care about

# Pivot wider so each macro variable becomes a column
macro_wide <- macro_long %>%
  select(country = country_code, year, series_clean, value) %>%
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = series_clean,
    values_from = value
  )

# Join with Compustat
full_df <- compustat_combined %>%
  left_join(macro_wide, by = c("fic" = "country", "fyear" = "year"))

# Filter fyear ≤ 2021
full_df <- full_df %>%
  filter(fyear <= 2020 & fyear >= 2009)

1.5 Data Handling

1.5.1 Handling missing values

As ESG scores are essential for analysis, all companies (based on gvkey) that have no values on any of the ESG dimensions across the entire sample period will be dropped.

# Define the ESG variable names
esg_vars <- c(
  "TRESGSOCOS", "TRESGCGVSS", "TRESGENERS", "ENSCORE",
  "TRESGENPIS", "TRESGCS", "TRESGCCS", "TRESGS", "CGSCORE",
  "TRESGSOHRS", "TRESGCGBDS", "TRESGSOPRS", "TRESGENRRS",
  "TRESGCGSRS", "SOSCORE", "TRESGSOWOS"
)

# Identify gvkeys with all Na ESG values across all rows and filter them out
drop_gvkeys <- full_df %>%
  group_by(gvkey) %>%
  summarise(all_na = all(rowSums(!is.na(across(all_of(esg_vars)))) == 0)) %>%
  filter(all_na) %>%
  pull(gvkey)

filtered_sample_df <- full_df %>%
  filter(!gvkey %in% drop_gvkeys)

1.5.2 Creating financial variables
# Compute variables
filtered_sample_df <- filtered_sample_df %>%
  arrange(gvkey, fyear) %>%
  group_by(gvkey) %>%
  mutate(
    size = at,
    roa = ni / at,
    tobins_q = (prcc_f * csho + dltt + dlc) / at,
    cfo_lag = lag(oancf / at),
    ppe_lag = lag(ppent / at),
    leverage_lag = lag(lt / at),
    inflation_lag = lag(inflation),
    gdp_growth_lag = lag(gdp_growth),
    interest_rate_lag = lag(interest_rate),
    unemployment_rate_lag = lag(unemployment_rate)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

# Convert size to USD
filtered_sample_df <- filtered_sample_df %>%
  left_join(exchange_rates_df, by = c("curcd", "fyear")) %>%
  mutate(
    size = case_when(
      curcd != "USD" ~ log(size / rate),
      TRUE ~ log(size) # If already in USD, just log it
    )
  ) %>%
  select(-rate)

write.csv(filtered_sample_df, file = paste0(dirData, "Final_Sample_Before_Winsorize.csv"), row.names = FALSE)

# Drop the useless variables
final_sample_df <- filtered_sample_df %>%
  select(
    -indfmt, -datadate, -at, -che, -ebit, -ebitda, -lt, -oancf, -ppent, -revt, -exchg, -fyr, -price_year, -sedol, -isin, -loc, -sic, -tic, -prcc_f, -csho, -dltt, -dlc, -ni, -gdp_current_usd, -gdp_growth, -unemployment_rate, -inflation, -TRDIRCS, -TRDIRDS, -TRDIRIS, -TRDIRPDS, -TRDIRS,
  )

1.5.6 Winsorization
# Winsorize extreme values (at the 1st and 99th percentiles)
winsorize <- function(x, lower_quantile = 0.01, upper_quantile = 0.99) {
  lower <- quantile(x, lower_quantile, na.rm = TRUE)
  upper <- quantile(x, upper_quantile, na.rm = TRUE)
  x <- pmax(x, lower)
  x <- pmin(x, upper)
  return(x)
}

final_sample_df <- final_sample_df %>%
  mutate(across(
    c(size, roa, tobins_q, cfo_lag, ppe_lag, leverage_lag),
    ~ ifelse(is.infinite(.x) | is.nan(.x), NA, .x)
  )) %>%
  mutate(
    size = winsorize(size),
    roa = winsorize(roa),
    tobins_q = winsorize(tobins_q),
    cfo_lag = winsorize(cfo_lag),
    ppe_lag = winsorize(ppe_lag),
    leverage_lag = winsorize(leverage_lag)
  )
# Define 6 distinct shades of green
green_shades <- c("#00441B", "#006D2C", "#238B45", "#41AB5D", "#74C476", "#A1D99B")

# Common theme for thesis
thesis_theme <- theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = 10)),
    axis.title.y = element_text(margin = margin(r = 10)),
    plot.title = element_blank()
  )

# Helper function to make histograms with cutoff lines & custom axis label
plot_hist_with_cutoffs <- function(data, var, fill_color, x_label) {
  lower_cut <- quantile(data[[var]], 0.01, na.rm = TRUE)
  upper_cut <- quantile(data[[var]], 0.99, na.rm = TRUE)

  ggplot(data, aes_string(x = var)) +
    geom_histogram(bins = 30, fill = fill_color, color = "white") +
    geom_vline(xintercept = lower_cut, linetype = "dashed", color = "black", linewidth = 0.3) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = upper_cut, linetype = "dashed", color = "black", linewidth = 0.3) +
    labs(x = x_label, y = "Frequency") +
    thesis_theme
}

# Create histograms with better axis titles
p1 <- plot_hist_with_cutoffs(final_sample_df, "size", green_shades[1], "Firm Size (log assets)")
p2 <- plot_hist_with_cutoffs(final_sample_df, "roa", green_shades[2], "ROA")
p3 <- plot_hist_with_cutoffs(final_sample_df, "tobins_q", green_shades[3], "Tobin's Q")
p4 <- plot_hist_with_cutoffs(final_sample_df, "cfo_lag", green_shades[4], "Cash Flow from Operations (lagged)")
p5 <- plot_hist_with_cutoffs(final_sample_df, "ppe_lag", green_shades[5], "Property, Plant & Equipment Ratio (lagged)")
p6 <- plot_hist_with_cutoffs(final_sample_df, "leverage_lag", green_shades[6], "Leverage (lagged)")

# Arrange plots

2.1.3 Recipe for Random Forest
# Random Forest Recipe
reg_recipe_rf <- recipe(
  tobins_q ~ emissions + resource_use + environmental_innovation + human_rights + product_responsibility + workforce + community + management + shareholders + csr_strategy + size + rule_of_law + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag + unemployment_rate_lag,
  data = train_set
) %>%
  step_naomit(all_predictors(), all_outcomes()) %>%
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  step_zv(all_predictors())

2.2 Model Training

2.2.1 Model specifications
# Define the RF model with tuning grid
rf_model_spec <-
  rand_forest(mtry = tune(), trees = 100, min_n = tune()) |>
  set_mode("regression") |>
  set_engine("ranger", importance = "permutation")
2.2.2 Workflows set-up
# Random Forest
rf_tune_wf <-
  workflow() |>
  add_recipe(reg_recipe_rf) |>
  add_model(rf_model_spec)

2.3 Hyperparameter Tuning

2.3.1 Tuning grid and metrics

There are 18 features in the recipe, so the value of mtry will be tuned on values from 1 to 18.

# Random Forest Grid
grid_rf <-
  grid_regular(
    mtry(range = c(1, 18)),
    min_n(range = c(5, 20)),
    levels = 18
  )

foreach::getDoParWorkers()
## [1] 1
2.3.2 Tuning the hyperparameter
reg_metrics <- metric_set(rmse, rsq, mae)

# Use parallel processing to speed up computation:
num_cores <- parallel::detectCores()
num_cores
## [1] 10
doParallel::registerDoParallel(cores = num_cores - 1L)

# RF Tuning
rf_tune <- tune_grid(
  rf_tune_wf,
  resamples = folds,
  grid = grid_rf,
  metrics = reg_metrics,
  control = control_grid(verbose = TRUE, save_pred = TRUE)
)
2.3.3 Plot the tuning results
# Random Forest Metrics Plot with consistent style and more space between facets
rf_tune_metrics <- rf_tune |> collect_metrics()

rf_tune_plot <- autoplot(rf_tune) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = 10)),
    axis.title.y = element_text(margin = margin(r = 10)),
    legend.position = "right",
    panel.spacing = unit(0.7, "cm") # Increase white space between facet panels
  )

# Save plot
ggsave(
  filename = paste0(dirRslt, "rf_tune_metrics.png"),

)

2.4.2 Permutation Feature Importance
# Define variable groups
top5_esg_components_vars <- c("resource_use", "emissions", "workforce", "community", "csr_strategy")
financial_vars <- c("cfo_lag", "ppe_lag", "leverage_lag", "size")
macroeconomic_vars <- c("rule_of_law", "gdp_growth_lag", "inflation_lag", "unemployment_rate_lag")
esg_components_vars <- c("product_responsibility", "management", "human_rights", "environmental_innovation", "shareholders")

# Extract and prepare variable importance data
vi_df <- rf_final_fit %>%
  extract_fit_parsnip() %>%
  pluck("fit") %>%
  vi()

# Categorize each variable
vi_df <- vi_df %>%
  mutate(
    group = case_when(
      Variable %in% top5_esg_components_vars ~ "Top 5 ESG",
      Variable %in% esg_components_vars ~ "Other ESG",
      Variable %in% financial_vars ~ "Financial",
      Variable %in% macroeconomic_vars ~ "Macroeconomic",
      TRUE ~ "Other"
    ),
    alpha = if_else(group == "Top 5 ESG", 1, 0.5),
    size = if_else(group == "Top 5 ESG", 0.5, 0.3)
  )

# Custom color palette
group_colors <- c(
  "Top 5 ESG" = "#006E01",
  "Other ESG" = "#009E39",
  "Financial" = "gray20",
  "Macroeconomic" = "gray80",
  "Other" = "gray50"
)

# Plot
vi_plot <- ggplot(vi_df, aes(x = reorder(Variable, Importance), y = Importance)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = group, alpha = alpha, linewidth = size), color = "black") +
  geom_text(
    data = filter(vi_df, group == "Top 5 ESG"),
    aes(label = round(Importance, 2)),
    hjust = -0.1,
    size = 3
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = group_colors) +
  scale_alpha_identity() +
  scale_linewidth_identity() +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(
    x = "Variable",
    y = "Importance",
    fill = "Variable Group"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = 10)),
    axis.title.y = element_text(margin = margin(r = 10)),
    legend.position = "bottom"
  )

# Save plot
ggsave(
  filename = paste0(dirRslt, "rf_variable_importance.png"),
  plot = vi_plot, width = 8, height = 6, dpi = 600

3. Propensity Score Matching (PSM)

3.1 Preparing Firm-level Data for PSM

3.1.1 Dropping incomplete data firms
esg_new_vars <- c("esg_overall", "governance_pillar", "environment_pillar", "social_pillar")

# Drop firms with missing values
drop_gvkeys <- DiD_df %>%
  group_by(gvkey) %>%
  summarise(any_na = any(rowSums(is.na(across(all_of(esg_new_vars)))) > 0)) %>%
  filter(any_na) %>%
  pull(gvkey)

DiD_df <- DiD_df %>%
  filter(!gvkey %in% drop_gvkeys)

DiD_df %>%
  summarise(unique_gvkeys = n_distinct(gvkey))
##   unique_gvkeys
## 1           780
3.1.2 Dropping duplicates and sanity check for 12 firm-years observations
# Remove duplicate firm-year rows
DiD_df_cleaned <- DiD_df %>%
  distinct(gvkey, fyear, .keep_all = TRUE)

# Check number of years per gvkey
firm_counts <- DiD_df_cleaned %>%
  filter(fyear >= 2009, fyear <= 2020) %>%
  group_by(gvkey) %>%
  summarise(n_years = n(), .groups = "drop")

# Identify gvkeys with less than 12 years
incomplete_firms <- firm_counts %>%
  filter(n_years < 12)

print(incomplete_firms)

DiD_df <- DiD_df_cleaned %>%
  filter(!(gvkey %in% incomplete_firms$gvkey))

table(table(DiD_df$gvkey))

3.1.3 Convert size to USD
# Adjust size if currency is not already in USD and log-transform
DiD_df <- DiD_df %>%
  left_join(exchange_rates_df, by = c("curcd", "fyear")) %>%
  mutate(
    size = case_when(
      curcd != "USD" ~ log(size / rate),
      TRUE ~ log(size) # If already in USD, just log it
    )
  ) %>%
  select(-rate)
3.1.4 Aggregating firm-level covariates (pre-2015)
# Build firm-level dataset for PSM
firm_level_df <- DiD_df %>%
  filter(fyear < 2015) %>%
  group_by(gvkey) %>%
  summarise(
    dTreat = first(dTreat),
    size = mean(size, na.rm = TRUE),
    leverage_lag = mean(leverage_lag, na.rm = TRUE),
    cfo_lag = mean(cfo_lag, na.rm = TRUE),
    ppe_lag = mean(ppe_lag, na.rm = TRUE),
  )

# Drop firms with NA in covariates
firm_level_df <- firm_level_df %>%
  drop_na()

3.2 Running PSM

3.2.1 Defining PSM models & calipers
# Define PSM variables
psm_vars_core <- c("size", "ppe_lag", "cfo_lag", "leverage_lag")

# Run matching
final_m.out <- MatchIt::matchit(
  cobalt::f.build("dTreat", firm_level_df[, psm_vars_core]),
  data = firm_level_df,
  method = "optimal",
  replace = FALSE,
  caliper = 0.01,
)

# Summary of matching
summary(final_m.out)

3.2.2 PSM Balance Table
# Create matched data
matched_df <- match.data(final_m.out)

# Initialize balance results list
psm_balance_tbl <- purrr::map_dfr(psm_vars_core, function(var) {
  # Means before matching
  treat_mean_unmatched <- mean(firm_level_df[[var]][firm_level_df$dTreat == 1], na.rm = TRUE)
  control_mean_unmatched <- mean(firm_level_df[[var]][firm_level_df$dTreat == 0], na.rm = TRUE)
  t_test_unmatched <- t.test(firm_level_df[[var]] ~ firm_level_df$dTreat)

  # Means after matching
  treat_mean_matched <- mean(matched_df[[var]][matched_df$dTreat == 1], na.rm = TRUE)
  control_mean_matched <- mean(matched_df[[var]][matched_df$dTreat == 0], na.rm = TRUE)
  t_test_matched <- t.test(matched_df[[var]] ~ matched_df$dTreat)

  # Combine into data frame
  tibble(
    Variable = var,
    Match_Status = c("Unmatched", "Matched"),
    Treated_Mean = c(treat_mean_unmatched, treat_mean_matched),
    Control_Mean = c(control_mean_unmatched, control_mean_matched),
    `T-C` = c(
      treat_mean_unmatched - control_mean_unmatched,
      treat_mean_matched - control_mean_matched
    ),
    `P-Value` = c(t_test_unmatched$p.value, t_test_matched$p.value)
  )
})

# Format and print nicely
psm_balance_tbl %>%
  mutate(
    Treated_Mean = round(Treated_Mean, 3),
    Control_Mean = round(Control_Mean, 3),
    `T-C` = round(`T-C`, 3),
    `P-Value` = formatC(`P-Value`, digits = 3, format = "f")
  ) %>%
  knitr::kable("latex", booktabs = TRUE, caption = "PSM Covariate Balance Table (Before and After Matching)") %>%
  kableExtra::kable_styling(latex_options = c("hold_position", "striped"))

# Prepare data → aggregate ROA per year per group
roa_plot_data <- DiD_df %>%
  filter(fyear >= 2009, fyear <= 2020) %>%

4.2 H1 ESG and CFP Association

# Check balance
is.pbalanced(final_panel_df)
## [1] TRUE
# H1 model formula
h1_model_tq <- tobins_q ~ esg_overall + size + rule_of_law + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag +
  inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag + unemployment_rate_lag

# Model 1: Pooled OLS
h1_rslts_pool <- plm(h1_model_tq, data = final_panel_df, model = "pooling")

# Model 2: Fixed Effects (Within)
h1_rslts_fe <- plm(h1_model_tq, data = final_panel_df, model = "within")

# Model 3: Between Effects
h1_rslts_bw <- plm(h1_model_tq, data = final_panel_df, model = "between")

# Model 4: Random Effects
h1_rslts_re <- plm(h1_model_tq, data = final_panel_df, model = "random")

# Cluster-robust standard errors
se_pool <- coeftest(h1_rslts_pool, vcovHC(h1_rslts_pool, cluster = "group", type = "HC1"))
se_fe <- coeftest(h1_rslts_fe, vcovHC(h1_rslts_fe, cluster = "group", type = "HC1"))
se_re <- coeftest(h1_rslts_re, vcovHC(h1_rslts_re, cluster = "group", type = "HC1"))

# Stargazer table
stargazer(
  h1_rslts_pool, h1_rslts_fe, h1_rslts_bw, h1_rslts_re,
  se = list(
    se_pool[, "Std. Error"],
    se_fe[, "Std. Error"],
    NULL,
    se_re[, "Std. Error"]
  ),
  type = "text",
  title = "Panel Models: ESG → Tobin's Q (H1)",
  column.labels = c("Pooled OLS", "Fixed Effects", "Between", "Random Effects"),
  dep.var.labels = "Tobin's Q",
  omit.stat = c("f", "ser"),
  digits = 3,
  no.space = TRUE,
  star.cutoffs = c(0.1, 0.05, 0.01),
  notes = c("* p < 0.1; ** p < 0.05; *** p < 0.01")
)

# F test: compare fixed effects and pooled models
ftest <- pooltest(h1_rslts_pool, h1_rslts_fe)
print(ftest)
## 
##  F statistic
## 
## data:  h1_model_tq
## F = 32.307, df1 = 435, df2 = 4737, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: unstability
# Hausman Test: FE vs RE
hausman_test <- phtest(h1_rslts_fe, h1_rslts_re)
print(hausman_test)
## 
##  Hausman Test
## 
## data:  h1_model_tq
## chisq = 277.6, df = 9, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: one model is inconsistent
# Create the results table
model_tests <- data.frame(
  Test = c("F-test", "Hausman test"),
  Comparison = c("Pooled OLS vs Fixed Effects", "Fixed Effects vs Random Effects"),
  Statistic = c(round(ftest$statistic, 3), round(hausman_test$statistic, 3)),
  df = c(
    paste0("(", ftest$parameter[1], ", ", ftest$parameter[2], ")"),
    as.character(hausman_test$parameter)
  ),
  p_value = c(
    format.pval(ftest$p.value, digits = 3, eps = .001),
    format.pval(hausman_test$p.value, digits = 3, eps = .001)
  )
)

# Print table using knitr::kable
kable(model_tests,
  format = "latex", # Use "markdown" for HTML/PDF flex output
  caption = "Model Specification Tests for Panel Data",
  align = c("l", "l", "r", "r", "r"),
  booktabs = TRUE
)

model_esg <- esg_overall ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey) + factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

rslts_esg <- lm(model_esg, data = final_panel_df)

4.3.2 ESG Components Scores
# Model 1: Emissions
model_emissions <- emissions ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey) +
  factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

rslts_emissions <- lm(model_emissions, data = final_panel_df, na.action = na.exclude)

summary(rslts_emissions)

se_emissions <- coeftest(rslts_emissions, vcov = vcovCL(rslts_emissions, cluster = ~gvkey))[, "Std. Error"]

# Model 2: Workforce
model_workforce <- workforce ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey) +
  factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

rslts_workforce <- lm(model_workforce, data = final_panel_df, na.action = na.exclude)

summary(rslts_workforce)

# Model 3: Community
model_community <- community ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey) +
  factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

rslts_community <- lm(model_community, data = final_panel_df, na.action = na.exclude)

summary(rslts_community)

# Model 4: Resource Use
model_resource <- resource_use ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey) +
  factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

rslts_resource <- lm(model_resource, data = final_panel_df, na.action = na.exclude)

summary(rslts_resource)

# Model 5: CSR Strategy
model_csr <- csr_strategy ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey) +
  factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

rslts_csr <- lm(model_csr, data = final_panel_df, na.action = na.exclude)

summary(rslts_csr)

# Stargazer table
stargazer(
  rslts_emissions, rslts_resource, rslts_workforce, rslts_community,
  se = list(se_emissions, se_resource, se_workforce, se_community),
  type = "latex",
  title = "DiD Models with ESG Subdimensions as Dependent Variables",
  dep.var.labels = c("Emissions", "Resource Use", "Workforce", "Community"),
  omit = c(
    "factor\\(fyear\\)", "factor\\(gvkey\\)", "factor\\(gsector\\)", "factor\\(fic\\)",
    "size", "cfo_lag", "ppe_lag", "leverage_lag",
    "inflation_lag", "gdp_growth_lag", "unemployment_rate_lag", "rule_of_law"
  ),
  omit.stat = c("ser", "f"),
  digits = 3,
  no.space = TRUE,
  star.cutoffs = c(0.1, 0.05, 0.01),
  notes.align = "l",
  notes = c("* p < 0.1; ** p < 0.05; *** p < 0.01"),
  label = "tab:DiD_ESG_subdimensions",
  float.env = "table",
  add.lines = list(
    c("Controls", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes"),
    c("Firm FE", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes"),
    c("Year FE", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes"),
    c("Sector FE", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes"),
    c("Country FE", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes"),
    c("Cluster SE (firm)", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes", "Yes")
  )
)

4.4 H3 & H4 DiD Model Recipes

# ROA Basic
model_ROA <- roa ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

# ROA Extended
model_ROA_ext <- roa ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  emissions + resource_use + workforce + community + csr_strategy + size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

# Tobin's Q Basic
model_TQ <- tobins_q ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat + cfo_lag + size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic)

# Tobin's Q Extended
model_TQ_ext <- tobins_q ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  emissions + resource_use + workforce + community + csr_strategy + size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic)
4.4.1 Run DiD Models for Matched Sample
# ROA Basic
rslts_ROA <- plm(model_ROA,
  data = final_panel_df, index = c("gvkey", "fyear"),
  model = "within", effect = "twoways"
)
summary(rslts_ROA)

4.4.2 Calculate robust Standard Errors for Matched Sample
# ROA Basic
roa_se <- coeftest(rslts_ROA, vcov. = vcovHC(rslts_ROA, type = "HC1", cluster = "group"))[, "Std. Error"]

# Tobin's Q Extended
tq_ext_se <- coeftest(rslts_TQ_ext, vcov. = vcovHC(rslts_TQ_ext, type = "HC1", cluster = "group"))[, "Std. Error"]

4.4.7 LM Models
# ROA Basic
model_ROA_lm <- roa ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic) + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey)
# ROA Extended
model_ROA_ext_lm <- roa ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  emissions + resource_use + workforce + community + csr_strategy +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic) + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey)

# Tobin's Q Basic
model_TQ_lm <- tobins_q ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic) + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey)

# Tobin's Q Extended
model_TQ_ext_lm <- tobins_q ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  emissions + resource_use + workforce + community + csr_strategy +
  size + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag + rule_of_law + factor(gsector) + factor(fic) + factor(fyear) + factor(gvkey)

rslts_ROA_lm <- lm(model_ROA_lm, data = final_panel_df)
summary(rslts_ROA_lm)

tq_se_lm <- coeftest(rslts_TQ_lm, vcov = vcovCL(rslts_TQ_lm, cluster = ~gvkey))[, "Std. Error"]
tq_ext_se_lm <- coeftest(rslts_TQ_ext_lm, vcov = vcovCL(rslts_TQ_ext_lm, cluster = ~gvkey))[, "Std. Error"]

  rslts_ROA_lm, rslts_ROA_ext_lm, rslts_TQ_lm, rslts_TQ_ext_lm,

)

4.5 Descriptive Statistics

4.5.1 Correlation Matrix
# Define variable list
DiD_vars_corr <- c(
  "esg_overall", "environment_pillar", "social_pillar", "governance_pillar",
  "emissions", "resource_use", "workforce", "community", "csr_strategy",
  "roa", "tobins_q", "size", "cfo_lag", "ppe_lag", "leverage_lag",
  "gdp_growth_lag", "unemployment_rate_lag", "inflation_lag", "rule_of_law"
)

# Compute correlation matrix with p-values
rc <- rcorr(as.matrix(DiD_df[, DiD_vars_corr]))
r <- rc$r
p <- rc$P

# Create matrix with proper dimnames
n <- length(DiD_vars_corr)
corr_star <- matrix("",
  nrow = n, ncol = n,
  dimnames = list(DiD_vars_corr, DiD_vars_corr)
)


for (i in 2:n) {
  for (j in 1:(i - 1)) {
    star <- ifelse(p[i, j] < 0.05, "*", "")
    corr_star[i, j] <- paste0(sprintf("%.2f", r[i, j]), star)
  }
}

# Keep only lower triangle
for (i in 1:(n - 1)) {
  for (j in (i + 1):n) {
    corr_star[i, j] <- ""
  }
}

# Convert to LaTeX table
latex_table <- xtable(corr_star)
align(latex_table) <- rep("l", n + 1) # left-align all columns

# Sanitize and print
print(latex_table,
  include.rownames = TRUE,
  include.colnames = FALSE,
  sanitize.text.function = identity,
  floating = TRUE,
  floating.environment = "table",
  table.placement = "ht",
  tabular.environment = "tabular",
  hline.after = c(-1, 0, n),
  comment = FALSE
)

4.5.1 Numeric variables
desc_vars <- c(
  "roa", "tobins_q", "emissions", "resource_use", "environmental_innovation", "human_rights", "product_responsibility", "workforce", "community", "management", "shareholders", "csr_strategy", "size", "rule_of_law", "cfo_lag", "ppe_lag", "leverage_lag", "inflation_lag", "gdp_growth_lag", "unemployment_rate_lag"
)

# Extract skim summary
skim_df <- skimr::skim(final_panel_df %>% select(all_of(desc_vars))) %>%
  filter(skim_type == "numeric") %>%
  select(
    Variable = skim_variable,
    N_missing = n_missing,
    Mean = numeric.mean,
    SD = numeric.sd,
    Min = numeric.p0,
    Median = numeric.p50,
    Max = numeric.p100
  )

# Compute actual N
total_N <- nrow(final_panel_df)

skim_df <- skim_df %>%
  mutate(N = total_N - N_missing) %>%
  select(Variable, N, Mean, SD, Min, Median, Max)

# Create LaTeX table
skim_df %>%
  kable(
    format = "latex", booktabs = TRUE, digits = 3,
    caption = "Descriptive Statistics for Main Variables in DiD Sample",
    label = "tab:desc_did"
  ) %>%
  kable_styling(latex_options = c("hold_position", "striped"))

  group_by(gsector) %>%
  summarise(N_unique_firms = n_distinct(gvkey)) %>%
  arrange(desc(N_unique_firms))

# Table 2: N per gind
gsector_table %>%
  kable(
    format = "latex", booktabs = TRUE,
    caption = "Number of Firm-Year Observations per Sector (gsector)",
    label = "tab:gsector_counts"
  ) %>%
  kable_styling(latex_options = c("hold_position", "striped"))

4.6 H5 DiD Moderation

4.6.1 DiD Regression with FS Sector Dummy Interaction
# Create FS dummy
final_panel_df <- final_panel_df %>%
  mutate(dFS = if_else(gsector == 40, 1, 0))

# Tobin's Q model
model_TQ_FS <- tobins_q ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  dFS + dPost:dFS + dPost:dTreat:dFS +
  esg_overall + rule_of_law + cfo_lag + ppe_lag +
  leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag

rslts_TQ_FS <- lm(model_TQ_FS, data = final_panel_df)

# ROA model
model_ROA_FS <- roa ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  dFS + dPost:dFS + dPost:dTreat:dFS +
  esg_overall + rule_of_law + cfo_lag + ppe_lag +
  leverage_lag + inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag +
  unemployment_rate_lag

rslts_ROA_FS <- lm(model_ROA_FS, data = final_panel_df)

# Clustered SEs (by gvkey)
se_TQ_FS <- sqrt(diag(vcovCL(rslts_TQ_FS, cluster = ~gvkey)))
se_ROA_FS <- sqrt(diag(vcovCL(rslts_ROA_FS, cluster = ~gvkey)))

# Table
stargazer(
  rslts_TQ_FS, rslts_ROA_FS,
  se = list(se_TQ_FS, se_ROA_FS),
  type = "latex",
  title = "DiD Regression with Financial Sector Interaction",
  dep.var.labels = c("Tobin's Q", "ROA"),
  omit = c(
    "factor\\(fyear\\)", "factor\\(gvkey\\)",
    "cfo_lag", "ppe_lag", "leverage_lag",
    "inflation_lag", "gdp_growth_lag", "unemployment_rate_lag", "rule_of_law"
  ),
  omit.stat = c("ser", "f"),
  digits = 3,
  no.space = TRUE,
  star.cutoffs = c(0.1, 0.05, 0.01),
  notes.align = "l",
  notes = c("* p < 0.1; ** p < 0.05; *** p < 0.01"),
  label = "tab:DiD_FS_results",
  float.env = "table"
)

4.6.3 DiD Regression with Strong Rule of Law Dummy Interaction
# Create Strong Rule of Law dummy
rule_median <- median(final_panel_df$rule_of_law, na.rm = TRUE)
final_panel_df <- final_panel_df %>%
  mutate(dStrongRule = if_else(rule_of_law >= rule_median, 1, 0))

# Tobin's Q model
model_TQ_Rule <- tobins_q ~ dPost + dTreat + dDirective + dPost:dTreat +
  dStrongRule + dPost:dStrongRule + dPost:dTreat:dStrongRule +
  esg_overall + cfo_lag + ppe_lag + leverage_lag +
  inflation_lag + gdp_growth_lag + unemployment_rate_lag

# ROA model
